  <description><![CDATA[<p>The beautiful Colonna Resort, designed in typical Sardinian style, lies in a tranquil location just outside the <a data-udi="umb://document/d3596b90f23e46bba95688a160933be3" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d3596b90f23e46bba95688a160933be3}" title="Costa Smeralda Area">Costa Smeralda's</a> most famous resort, <strong>Porto Cervo</strong>.</p>
<p>Boasting one of the biggest seawater pool areas in Europe, you are spoilt for choice with seven pools and a large sundeck area with a whirlpool offering a view of the sea - and as if that's not enough, you can also enjoy the lovely private sandy beach.</p>
<p>The <em>Colonna</em> restaurant on the 5th floor has a panoramic terrace with beautiful sea views where you can enjoy Mediterranean dishes under the stars. There is also the <em>Pagoda</em> restaurant set close to the pool and offers traditional local dishes served at lunch in buffet style. A beach bar and <em>Colonna Caffe</em> are open daily to refreshments. </p>
<p>The Wellness and Fitness centre spans across approximately, 1000m² and has a heated indoor seawater swimming pool and a Jacuzzi with water features. There is also a sauna and a relaxation area and a herbal team room. Equipped with a gym and massage rooms offering massages and treatments, (payable locally).  </p>]]></description>
